Tested with several strings, with the code below, the str.replace in while loop one is around twice faster.

```python
_ZERO_WIDTH_CHARS = "\u200b\u200c"
_RE_REMOVE_ZERO_WIDTHS = re.compile(f"[{_ZERO_WIDTH_CHARS}]+")
def rmz_re(text: str) -> str:
    return _RE_REMOVE_ZERO_WIDTHS.sub("", text)

def rmz_replace(text: str) -> str:
    for ch in _ZERO_WIDTH_CHARS:
        while ch in text:
            text = text.replace(ch, "")
    return text
```

