@emmanuelle 

> For the convex hull, the Feret diameter is defined on the convex hull.

The feret diameter is defined for any object, the convex hull just makes it faster to compute since the largest diameter must join two vertices of the hull. But the question is that whether "hull + feret on hull vertices" is faster than "feret on all vertices". I guess the former is faster for most data given existing implementations.

